      "side": 1,
      "message": "About mergeable - I have been tempted in the past to do API_REF_UPDATED_AND_CHANGE_REINDEX in https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/config-gerrit.html#change.mergeabilityComputationBehavior so that we can get mergeability. It would be useful in various places.\nBut I didn\u0027t want to risk slowing anything down, it would have been great if they had listed exactly what quantifies as a large repo or how many open changes are a lot in their docs.\n\nBack to this change-\nAny change to httputils is scary so upto you if it is worth plumbing in gitiles client instead of doing that.\nLGTM for current changes.",
